Question-

Given a number (as string) and two integers a and b, divide the string in two non-empty parts such that the first part is divisible by a 
and the second part is divisible by b. In case multiple answers exist, return the string such that the first non-empty part has minimum length.

 

Example 1:

Input:
1200 4 3
Output:
12 00
Explanation:
12 is divisible by 4, and
00 is divisible by 3.

Solution-

class Solution{
    static String stringPartition(String S, int a, int b){
        // code here
        int i=1;
        //boolean flag = false;
        String res = "";
        while(i<S.length()){
            String str1 = S.substring(0,i);
            String str2 = S.substring(i,S.length());
            
            int val1 = Integer.parseInt(str1);
            int val2 = Integer.parseInt(str2);
            
            if(val1%a == 0 && val2%b==0 ){
                res = str1+" "+str2;
                return res;
            }
            i++;
        }
        
        return "-1";
        
    }
}
